{"TopicId":186971,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How would you fake a \u0026quot;mission control\u0026quot; co-pilot?","CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-05T09:50:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-05T09:50:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EThis is not an add-on per se, because everything relies on external tools, but I think this is the best forum to post this.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having this idea of hosting a two-player game session where one of the players (player #1, aka \u0022pilot\u0022) is actually playing KSP (the whole mission in A.L.C.O.R. IVA with a VR headset) and there\u0027s a second player (player #2, aka \u0022mission control\u0022) who speaks to the first player and gives them guidance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlayer #2 sees what the player #1 sees (simply by looking at their screen) but I\u0027d like to make the conversation more immersive \u003Cstrong\u003Eby making player #2 talk to player #1\u00A0 through their headphones, and possibly add a voice effect to make it sound like a radio or walkie-talkie chat.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, two questions \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E- What voice chat system do you recommend\u003C/strong\u003E to use while KSP is running? Skype? Discord? Team speak? Doesn\u0027t matter?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E- what voice modifier would you use for the radio effect? \u003C/strong\u003E(there are a few third-party products, like those: \u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://windowsreport.com/change-voice-on-skype/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://windowsreport.com/change-voice-on-skype/ \u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAdditional question:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E- Is this a dumb idea\u003C/strong\u003E and is there a much simpler way of doing this?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"guesswho2778","CreatedById":170733,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-05T10:59:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat sounds like a very good idea but i dont know how one player being in a vr headset and one not being in one will go so i wish you luck and hope you you share the results with us\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-05T11:09:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223645952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565002780\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170733\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022guesswho2778\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, guesswho2778 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0i dont know how one player being in a vr headset and one not being in one will go\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve explained in the first post: There\u0027s really only \u003Cem\u003Eone \u003C/em\u003Eplayer, the one who plays KSP and wears the VR headset. The other \u0022player\u0022 doesn\u0027t have KSP running and is talking to player #1 through Skype/TeamSpeak/Discord (which is running on player #1\u0027s computer alongside KSP).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it turns out that this is very similar to what I described, and they use Discord :\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalSpaceProgram/comments/boktgb/anyone_willing_to_play_airport_style_ksp_similar/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalSpaceProgram/comments/boktgb/anyone_willing_to_play_airport_style_ksp_similar/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-05T11:10:57Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2019 11:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by jeancallisti\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"guesswho2778","CreatedById":170733,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-06T02:51:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223645960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565003343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E really only \u003Cem\u003Eone \u003C/em\u003Eplayer, the one who plays KSP and wears\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E the VR headset. The other \u0022player\u0022 doesn\u0027t have\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E KSP running and is talking to player #1 through Skype/TeamSpeak/Discord (which is\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Erunning on player #1\u0027s computer alongside KSP).\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assumed that one player would be in the map making maneuver nodes and guiding the other player sorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-06T04:48:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/172757-142-telemachus-continued-web-based-telemetry-and-cameras/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Etelemachus\u003C/a\u003E? just have to direct to IP other than 127.0.0.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-06T07:13:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646331\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565066920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190933\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zer0Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, zer0Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/172757-142-telemachus-continued-web-based-telemetry-and-cameras/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Etelemachus\u003C/a\u003E? just have to direct to IP other than 127.0.0.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent suggestion! Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646290\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565059872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170733\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022guesswho2778\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, guesswho2778 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assumed that one player would be in the map making maneuver nodes and guiding the other player sorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo need to be sorry \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E That would make sense, but since we\u0027re physically in the same room, player #2 can just peek at player #1\u0027s screen (player #1 won\u0027t even notice as he\u0027s wearing the VR headset). Also it\u0027s meant for beginners so there won\u0027t be complex manoeuvers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-06T07:14:02Z\u0022 title=\u002208/06/2019 07:14  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by jeancallisti\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"guesswho2778","CreatedById":170733,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-07T06:06:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646361\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565075612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut since we\u0027re physically in the same room\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nahh... yes that would make it simpler than doing it through discord and such...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-07T08:34:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646826\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565157976\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170733\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022guesswho2778\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, guesswho2778 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nahh... yes that would make it simpler than doing it through discord and such...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003EAGAIN\u003C/span\u003E:\u003C/strong\u003E The talk \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ewould \u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003Etake place through Discord, to benefit from voice effects like walkie-talkie effect or radio effect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nKSP = \u003Cstrong\u003EONE \u003C/strong\u003Ecomputer (player #2 looks at player #1 screen)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChat = \u003Cstrong\u003ETWO \u003C/strong\u003Ecomputers (player #2 talks to player #1 with a voice distortion effect)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK at this point it seems I\u0027m unable to explain what I\u0027m trying to achieve. Nevermind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"guesswho2778","CreatedById":170733,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-16T01:45:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646853\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565166859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/7/2019 at 6:04 PM, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK at this point it seems I\u0027m unable to explain what I\u0027m trying to achieve. Nevermind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nall good man i seem to have that problem with 90% of the stuff i say...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vossiewulf","CreatedById":179033,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-16T11:28:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d see if I could roll it back to 1.0ish and try the below. Add the right part to all your vehicle parts and the second player can keep you updated with all the telemetry they\u0027re receiving. Probably be an adventure just trying to get it to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022149963\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9603154403\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/118867-104-houston-v100-a-mission-control-ui-for-telemachus/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2130897\u0026amp;embedComment=2130897\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2130897\u0022 style=\u0022height:292px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-16T12:58:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223651375\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565954898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vossiewulf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, vossiewulf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d see if I could roll it back to 1.0ish and try the below. Add the right part to all your vehicle parts and the second player can keep you updated with all the telemetry they\u0027re receiving. Probably be an adventure just trying to get it to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022149963\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3361683771\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/118867-104-houston-v100-a-mission-control-ui-for-telemachus/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2130897\u0026amp;embedComment=2130897\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2130897\u0022 style=\u0022height:289px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, this was included right into the Telemachus release packages quite some time ago, IIRC.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSO you shouldnt have to download this seperately... Just install Telemachus and its in there.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*And*, IIRC, it mostly works\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DanGSun","CreatedById":185092,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-16T14:22:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223651417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565960319\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, this was included right into the Telemachus release packages quite some time ago, IIRC.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSO you shouldnt have to download this seperately... Just install Telemachus and its in there.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*And*, IIRC, it mostly works\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTelemachus is actually very laggy, when using it with KerbalVR, but I don\u0027t have enough time to rewrite Telemachus entirely...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223646331\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565066920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190933\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zer0Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/6/2019 at 5:48 AM, zer0Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/172757-142-telemachus-continued-web-based-telemetry-and-cameras/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Etelemachus\u003C/a\u003E? just have to direct to IP other than 127.0.0.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd this version is old and fully abandoned... So you should use \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179887-telemachus-reborn-ksp-v15x-17x/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E one instead.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-17T20:53:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI eventually went for the full shebang, with the multiplayer DMP server (to see the ship in spectator view), discord for the voice, Telemachus for the telemetry...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works surprisingly well. Since each of those uses a different kind of resource (GPU, network adapter, CPU...) they don\u0027t really impact the performance more than the impact that you\u0027d normally have with only VR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty cool\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-19T16:12:40Z\u0022 title=\u002208/19/2019 04:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by jeancallisti\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DanGSun","CreatedById":185092,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T22:17:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223652102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566075195\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/17/2019 at 9:53 PM, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI eventually went for the full shebang, with the multiplayer DMP server (to see the ship in spectator view), discord for the voice, Telemachus for the telemetry...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works surprisingly well. Since each of those uses a different kind of resource (GPU, network adapter, CPU...) they don\u0027t really impact the performance more than the impact that you\u0027d normally have with only VR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty cool\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou also can try ALCOR for advanced IVA)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T07:31:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you could do it the classic way and have\u00A0Mission Control use paper charts/graphs.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have also had this idea in the past and I am actually in the beginning stages of creating this:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlayer one (Pilot) (could include both a pilot and co-pilot)\u00A0is in a wooden-fabricated cockpit, entirely in IVA. Cannot see map except for charts, cannot view most of the HUD.\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlayer two (mission control)\u00A0is sitting nearby looking at a console much like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.pinimg.com/originals/cc/39/11/cc3911e9285beb30a13bc8e2134e7c97.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0one. Console is wired to the game but is kept separate from player one so that they are further apart and it adds realism.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223645933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564998649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/5/2019 at 5:50 AM, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E- Is this a dumb idea\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbsolutely not it sounds amazing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223645933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564998649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/5/2019 at 5:50 AM, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E- What voice chat system do you recommend\u003C/strong\u003E to use while KSP is running? Skype? Discord? Team speak? Doesn\u0027t matter?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDiscord, without a doubt. Highly immersive sound controls and settings, as well as crystal clear communication, as long as you have good mics.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-20T07:35:29Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2019 07:35  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Lo Var Lachland\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeancallisti","CreatedById":94406,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T08:13:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223654274\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566286315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lo Var Lachland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, Lo Var Lachland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlayer one (Pilot) (could include both a pilot and co-pilot)\u00A0is in a wooden-fabricated cockpit, entirely in IVA.Player two (mission control)\u00A0is sitting nearby looking at a console much like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.pinimg.com/originals/cc/39/11/cc3911e9285beb30a13bc8e2134e7c97.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell that would be living the dream\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T08:14:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223654309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566288804\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294406\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeancallisti\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, jeancallisti said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell that would be living the dream\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich I hope to be living at some point. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}